            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk Works fine both in terminal Vim and gVim. I'm in Arch Linux. Runing NeoVim in the same terminal yields the problem.\n\nI have a hunch it's a problem with NeoVim. I can confirm that if I do\n\n``` bash\ngrep -EHrin \"^M\" ./ | cut -d \":\" -f 1 | uniq | xargs sed -i \"s:^M::g\"\n```\n\nin my `.neovim` folder to remove all dos `^M` characters then it allows NeoVim to source everything properly. Shouldn't have to though.\n\nI'm basically building like this:\n\n``` bash\n  mkdir build && cd build\n  cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr ..\n  make\n```\n\nIs there something I may have missed?\n\nEDIT: Aha! I found the problem (or found a way to easily replicate it)! This is an issue of Vim and has carried on to NeoVim. Basically, you can replicate the issue like this: If you are in Linux, open up your vimrc, then do `:set fileformat=dos<cr>`, save and quit, then you'll get the errors next time you start vim. You can change it back to fileformat=unix and save it to fix it.\n\nThis might be something we want to fix in NeoVim.\n",
